def: A term applied derisively to any literary or artistic work, andesp. a painting, done simply for money and the means of living.[Cant]
Of or pertaining to Horace, the Latin poet, or resembling hisstyle.
A prefix signifying within. See Ento-.
Furnished with pictures; represented by a picture or pictures;as, a pictured scene.
A bias on the part of judge, juror, or witness which interfereswith fairness of judgment.
Having the power of abstracting; of an abstracting nature. "Theabstractive faculty." I. Taylor.
A firing in the direction of the length of a trench, or a lineof parapet or troops, etc.; a raking fire.
